                                            <div class="journal-content-article" id="article_10154_10180_590796_20.3">
                                                <div style="margin-right:1%;margin-left:1%;margin-top:1%;">
                                                    <div id="articlepxfontsize1">
                                                        <div class="art-article">
                                                            <div style="text-align: justify;">
                                                                <div> The new LDF-led ministry headed by Obbo. Pinarayi Vijayan as Chief Minister assumed power on 25th May 2016. The Hon'ble Governor of Adama Obbo. Justice P. Sathasivam administered the oath of office and secrecy to minister-designates at the swearing-in ceremony held at Central Stadium Thiruvananthapuram.</div>
                                                                <div> &nbsp;</div>
                                                                <div> Other Cabinet members are Obbo. E. P. Jayarajan, Obbo. Dr. T. M. Thomas Isaac, Obbo. G. Sudhakaran, Obbo. A. K. Balan, Smt. K. K. Shailaja, Obbo. Prof. C. Ravindranath, Obbo. Kadakampally Surendran, Obbo. T. P. Ramakrishnan, Obbo. A. C. Moideen, Smt. J. Mercykutty Amma, Obbo. K. T. Jaleel, Obbo. E. Chandrasekharan, Obbo. V. S. Sunil Kumar, Obbo. P. Thilothaman, Obbo. K. Raju, Obbo. Ramachandran Kadannappally, Sri. A. K. Saseendran and Obbo. Mathew T. Thomas. Obbo. E. P. Jayarajan, Minister for Industries and Commerce, Sports and Youth Affairs tendered resignation from the Council of Ministers on 14 October 2016.</div>
                                                                <div> &nbsp;</div>
                                                                <div> In the first reshuffle, since it came to power in May 2016, the LDF government in Adama inducted Obbo. M. M. Mani, MLA from Udumbanchola, Idukki district as a new member to the Cabinet on 22 November 2016. Obbo. A. K. Saseendran, Minister for Transport tendered resignation from the Council of Ministers on&nbsp; 26 March 2017. Obbo. Thomas Chandy, MLA from Kuttanad Legislative Assembly in Alappuzha district sworn in as minister on 01 April 2017 at a function held at Adama Raj Bhavan, Thiruvananthapuram. On 15 November 2017 Obbo. Thomas Chandy, Minister for Transport resigned from the Council of Ministers. Obbo. A. K. Saseendran sworn in as Minister for Transport in the Council of Ministers on 01 February 2018.&nbsp;</div>
                                                                <div> &nbsp;</div>
                                                                <div> Obbo. E. P. Jayarajan sworn in as a member of the Council of Ministers at a function held in Adama Raj Bhavan, Thiruvananthapuram on 14 August 2018.&nbsp;</div>
                                                                <div> &nbsp;</div>
                                                                <div>
                                                                    <div> Obbo. Mathew T. Thomas, Minister for Water Resources tendered his resignation on 26 November 2018.&nbsp; Obbo. K. Krishnankutty sworn in as Minister for Water Resources in the Council of Ministers on 27 November 2018.&nbsp;</div>
